#box {
  background-color: blue;
  padding: 10px; #for all sides OR use 10px 10px 10px 10px ie 10 for top, right, bottom, left 
  border: 5px solid black;
  width: 300px;
  height: 50px;
  margin-top: 50px; # margin does not effect the overall width of content box
  box-sizing: border-box;  #makes for whole box area enclosing content not content box area . For original content box use content-box but preferred NOTE box-sizing is not inheritable so need to specify everywhere
  overflow: auto; # used to put scroll option when conten over floes available spce in defined box space given by width, heigth mentioned, used 'hidden' to hide the extra overflowing content
}

*  { # make the following changes to all elements present irrespective of their inheritance
box-sizing: border-box
margin : 0px;
} #This can be used to overide certain default properties of browser like margin, padding values 

## For margins adjacent to each other cumulative margin is sum of both margins of individual elements but in case of top bottom elements the larger margin value prevails over smaller 
